      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted E92 M3, powered by the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power unit features individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system, delivering peak torque with a visceral 8,400 RPM redline. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by M-specific aluminum suspension components and a functional M Variable Differential Lock for optimal corner-exit traction. This example features the sought-after 6-speed manual transmission, offering a short-throw shift action and precise clutch take-up. Preventative maintenance is up to date, including addressed rod bearings and throttle actuators, ensuring the structural integrity of the rotating assembly. The hydraulic steering rack remains communicative, and the braking system retains strong initial bite with no signs of rotor glazing. An excellent specimen for the driver who prioritizes mechanical pedigree and atmospheric performance.",
